Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Gastrodin in Pure and Mixed Solvents at 273.15-313.15 K and Its Correlation with Different Thermodynamic Models
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of gastrodin in pure and mixed solvents was determined by using the isothermal saturation method at temperatures ranging from (273.15 to 313.15) K under 101.0 kPa. At all studied temperature, the solubility data obey the following order: 1,4-dioxane greater than ethyl acetate greater than toluene greater than cyclohexanone greater than isopropanol greater than acetone greater than ethanol greater than n-propanol greater than acetonitrile greater than 1-butanol greater than cyclohexane. In mixture of (ethyl acetate + ethanol), it increases firstly and then decreases with the increasing mass fraction of cosolvent. The composition dependence of the solubility has a maximum at around w = 0.8. The solubility data in pure and mixed solvents were correlated by modified Apelblat equation, h equation, Jouyban-Acree model and CNIBS/R-K model. In pure solvent, the largest RMSD value is 5.710-5, which is obtained in h equation, the RAD values are all less than 6.77%. In mixed solvents, the RAD data between the experimental and calculated values by Jouyban-Acree model is a little larger, 5.27%, and the RMSD value is 3.2210-4. However, with CNIBS/R-K model, the maximum RAD value obtained by the CNIBS/R-K model is 2.68% and the RMSD value is 7.110-5. CNIBS/R-K model is better
